      <trans-unit id="11028" identifier="7a3f474f96b41f8444cfc0a314a5578c">
        <source>Each of the cards in this activity represents a bit inside a digital device.</source>
        <target>crwdns11028:0crwdne11028:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[6]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11029" identifier="b68bacb26eaef236cd7a2342d96c7163">
        <source>When we arrange all of our ‘bits’ together in the square this is a representation of some data (admittedly random data in the magic trick, but it could be done with real data!).</source>
        <target>crwdns11029:0crwdne11029:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[6]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11030" identifier="c281152544e4b50e2aaf2e037765ad76">
        <source>This means our grid is an abstraction because it is a model that could be used to represent any piece of data that can be stored on a digital device, for example a sound file, a video, or even a piece of code!</source>
        <target>crwdns11030:0crwdne11030:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[6]</note>
      </trans-unit>
