      <trans-unit id="11056" identifier="4013b12e0c4dab4fc01066a997663c3a">
        <source>Ask students “What kind of errors can be detected and corrected with the parity cards?</source>
        <target>crwdns11056:0crwdne11056:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[19]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11057" identifier="24b46a095064de2cf7417b0dc42398fe">
        <source>At what point can you only detect but not correct and error?</source>
        <target>crwdns11057:0crwdne11057:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p[19]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11058" identifier="aa36b015adc396acf3643e9ed847bdd9">
        <source>Why is that?”
Can students explain what goes wrong when we try to detect the error if two cards are flipped?</source>
