      <trans-unit id="11061" identifier="22950bf352074c92e69fb473b87afe63">
        <source>Flipping a card will always change a row/column from odd to even, no matter what the card is in what the other cards in the row/column are.</source>
        <target>crwdns11061:0crwdne11061:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /p[22]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11062" identifier="3ab5187882c4857ff967291e5f7160a2">
        <source>Also, the idea that the corner card is correct for both the new row and column is an advanced concept, but a pattern that some students might recognise.</source>
        <target>crwdns11062:0crwdne11062:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /p[23]</note>
